  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>In RepairQ, a Billing Agent is the entity that assumes financial responsibility for products and services provided to a third party. Billing Agents are usually businesses, organizations, schools, and warranty providers. Invoicing gives your company tools to manage customers and corporate clients with net terms and is available to users on our Advanced and Professional plans.</p><h3 id=\"Invoicing:CreatingBillingAgents-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934196827/Invoicing+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934196827\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Invoicing Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934196840/Invoicing+Creating+and+Managing+Invoices\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934196840\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Invoicing: Creating and Managing Invoices</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934327961/Invoicing+Remittance+and+Reconciling+Invoices\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934327961\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Invoicing: Remittance and Reconciling Invoices</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934327935/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Invoicing:CreatingBillingAgents-CreatingaBillingAgent\">Creating a Billing Agent</h2><p /><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Customers</strong> \u2192 <strong>Billing</strong> <strong>Agents</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"557\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934327935/Billing%20Agents%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Billing Agents management page, click the <strong>Add button</strong> on the right side of the page. Once you are satisfied with the entry, click <strong>Save</strong> to add the billing agent to the list.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934327935/Billing%20Agents%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: If this is your first time creating a billing agent, click <strong>Add your first billing agent</strong>.</p><p /><p>3. Begin filling out the information for the new billing agent.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"442\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934327935/Billing%20Agents%203.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Company Details</strong> - Enter the Company name and address and the contact details.</p></li><li><p><strong>Is Deactivated</strong> - Select this option and save changes to deactivate and remove the Billing Agent from the agent management list.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934327935/Billing%20Agents%204.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Billing Agent Credit Limit</strong> - This is a line of credit issued to the agent. An agent can hold a negative balance up to the limit that you specify. This will allow the billing agent to hold a negative amount up to that limit. This credit can be used by selecting the Store Credit payment method when taking payment.</p></li><li><p><strong>Prefers Bulk Invoices</strong> - If selected, the default when creating an invoice will be to send a single invoice for all tickets listed. If not selected, the default will be to invoice each ticket separately with sequential invoice numbers. Invoice email notifications can be set up under <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933246465/Automated+Notification+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933246465\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Automated Notifications</a>.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Term Length in Days</strong> - Enter the billing term (cycle) in days for when the invoice will be due from the customer.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Hide Totals from Customer</strong> - When selected, this will remove any totals from the invoice and only show items and quantities.</p></li><li><p><strong>Enable Wholesale Pricing (Cost Plus Markup) </strong>- When a Billing Agent is flagged for wholesale pricing, items will be sold at cost + markup on tickets. This can be overridden by Item Type.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Cost Markup (%)</strong> - If Wholesale Pricing is enabled, enter the markup percentage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Item Type</strong> - If Wholesale Pricing is enabled, select which item type(s) will carry the markup.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h2 id=\"Invoicing:CreatingBillingAgents-ManagingBillingAgents\">Managing Billing Agents</h2><p>When viewing the Billing Agent management page, you can see basic details at a glance including contact information, counts of customers and/or tickets that have this agent assigned to them, ticket amount, and the last ticket date. The filters on this page allow you to search for Billing Agents by keyword and filter for deactivated agents. Under the Actions column, the Options button includes options to view or edit the Billing Agent. If the agent has never been assigned to a customer or ticket, it can be deleted.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934327935/Billing%20Agents%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>The Billing Agent View page provides more detailed information about the customers, tickets, and any credit transactions for that Billing Agent.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934327935/Billing%20Agents%207.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
